1. Project Architecture
a. Frontend: React.js
Build a dynamic, responsive UI with components for user interactions.
Use React Router for seamless navigation.
b. Backend: Node.js with Express.js
Create RESTful APIs for handling requests like fetching stock, managing orders, and user authentication.
c. Database: MongoDB
Store product details, user profiles, order histories, and custom designs.
d. Deployment
Frontend: Host with Netlify or Vercel.
Backend: Deploy using Heroku or AWS.
Database: Use MongoDB Atlas for cloud hosting.
2. Detailed Features in MERN
a. Buy Stationery Items
Frontend:
A product catalog with categories and a search bar.
Filter options for price, category, or availability.
Backend:
API: /products (GET) to fetch product list.
API: /order (POST) to place orders.
b. Pre-order Customized Stationery
Frontend:
Interactive tool for design (e.g., Canvas in React).
Form to upload designs or text customization.
Backend:
API: /custom-orders (POST) to handle uploads and store order details.
c. Check Available Stock
Frontend:
Live updates with React state management.
Stock alerts for low inventory.
Backend:
API: /stock (GET) to fetch real-time data.
Database: Update stock dynamically on order confirmation.
3. Authentication
Use JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for secure user sessions.
Implement role-based access (e.g., Admin for inventory management).
4. Payment Integration
Use services like Razorpay or Stripe for seamless transactions.
Include payment history in user profiles.
5. Additional Tools
State Management: Use Redux or Context API for global state handling.
Styling: Tailwind CSS or Material-UI for an elegant design.
Testing: Jest/React Testing Library for frontend; Mocha for backend.
